          policy00:
              'Mayura knows that you care how information about you is collected, used, and disclosed, and we appreciate your trust that we will do so carefully and sensibly. We take your privacy seriously and are committed to complying with all data protection laws that are applicable to us. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and disclose the data we collect and receive during the course of providing the Mayura Services. We only collect, use, and disclose your data in accordance with this Privacy Policy. \n\nWe may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes we make to this Privacy Policy in the future will be posted on this page and, where appropriate, notified to you by email, whereupon your continued use of Mayura Services shall constitute your acknowledgment and acceptance of the changes we make to this Privacy Policy.',

          policy01:
              "We may collect the following data from you: (a) identity, such as your name, gender, and date of birth; (b) contact, such as billing address, delivery address, email address, and phone number; (c) account, such as bank account and payment details; (d) transaction, such as details about payments to and from you, and other details of products and services you have purchased from us; (e) technical, such as internet protocol (IP) address, your login data, browser type and version, time zone setting and location, browser plug-in types and versions, operating system and platform, and other technology on the devices you use to access Mayura; (f) profile, such as your username and password, purchases or orders made by you, your interests, preferences, feedback and survey responses; (g) usage, such as information on how you use the Mayura Services; and (h) marketing and communications, such as your preferences in receiving marketing from us and our third parties and your communication preferences.\n\nAdditionally, during the course of your use of the Mayura Services, we may receive data  from you in the following situations: (a) when you create an account with us; (b) when you apply for any of the Mayura Services or purchase any products available on Mayura; (c) when you use any of the features or functions available on Mayura; (d) when you subscribe to Mayura publications or marketing collaterals; (e) when you enter a competition, promotion, or survey; (f) when you log in to your Mayura account or otherwise interact with us via an external service or application, such as Facebook or Google; and (g) when you interact with us offline, including when you interact with our Customer Service Team.\n\nYou must only submit data which is accurate and not misleading and you must keep it up to date and inform us of changes. We shall have the right to request for documentation to verify the data provided by you as part of our customer verification processes.\n\nWe will only be able to collect data if you voluntarily submit data to us. Unfortunately, if you choose not to submit data to us or subsequently withdraw your consent to our use of your data, we may not be able to provide you with the Mayura Services.\n\nYou may access and update your information submitted to us at any time.\n\nIf you provide data of any third party to us, you represent and warrant that you have obtained the necessary consent from that third party to share and transfer their data to us, and for us to collect, use, and disclose that data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.\n\nIf you sign up for Mayura using your social media account, link your Mayura account to your social media account, or use certain other Mayura social media features, we may access data about you which you have voluntarily provided to your social media provider in accordance with the provider\'s policies, and we will manage your data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.",
          policy02:
              "The data we collect may be used by us and/or shared with or transferred to third parties (including related companies, third party service providers and their service providers and related companies, and third party sellers), for some or all of the following purposes: (a) to facilitate your use of the Mayura Services, including responding to your queries, feedback, claims, or disputes through our Customer Service Team; (b) to process orders you submit through Mayura, whether the products are sold by us or a third party seller; (c) payments that you make through Mayura for products, whether sold by us or a third party seller, will be processed by our agent; (d) to deliver the products you have purchased through Mayura, whether sold by us or a third party seller (we may pass your information on to a third party in order to make delivery of the product to you, whether the product is sold through Mayura by us or a third party seller; (e) to update you on the delivery of the products, whether sold through Mayura by us or a third party seller, and for customer support purposes; (f) to compare information and verify with third parties in order to ensure that the information is accurate; (g) to administer your account (if any) with us; (h) to verify and carry out financial transactions in relation to payments you make online; (i) to audit the downloading of data from Mayura; (j) to improve the layout or content of the pages of Mayura and customise them for users; (k) to identify visitors to Mayura; (l) to carry out research on our users’ demographics and behaviour; (m) to provide you with information we think you may find useful or which you have requested from us, including information about our or third party sellers’ products and services, provided you have indicated that you have not objected to being contacted for these purposes; (n) subject to having obtained your consent in accordance with applicable law, we may also use your information to send you marketing or promotional materials about our or third party sellers’ products and services from time to time; and (o) we may also conduct automated-decision making processes in accordance with any of these purposes.The data we collect may be used by us and/or shared with or transferred to third parties (including related companies, third party service providers and their service providers and related companies, and third party sellers), for some or all of the following purposes: (a) to facilitate your use of the Mayura Services, including responding to your queries, feedback, claims, or disputes through our Customer Service Team; (b) to process orders you submit through Mayura, whether the products are sold by us or a third party seller; (c) payments that you make through Mayura for products, whether sold by us or a third party seller, will be processed by our agent; (d) to deliver the products you have purchased through Mayura, whether sold by us or a third party seller (we may pass your information on to a third party in order to make delivery of the product to you, whether the product is sold through Mayura by us or a third party seller; (e) to update you on the delivery of the products, whether sold through Mayura by us or a third party seller, and for customer support purposes; (f) to compare information and verify with third parties in order to ensure that the information is accurate; (g) to administer your account (if any) with us; (h) to verify and carry out financial transactions in relation to payments you make online; (i) to audit the downloading of data from Mayura; (j) to improve the layout or content of the pages of Mayura and customise them for users; (k) to identify visitors to Mayura; (l) to carry out research on our users’ demographics and behaviour; (m) to provide you with information we think you may find useful or which you have requested from us, including information about our or third party sellers’ products and services, provided you have indicated that you have not objected to being contacted for these purposes; (n) subject to having obtained your consent in accordance with applicable law, we may also use your information to send you marketing or promotional materials about our or third party sellers’ products and services from time to time; and (o) we may also conduct automated-decision making processes in accordance with any of these purposes.\n\nYou may unsubscribe from receiving marketing information at any time by using the unsubscribe function within the electronic marketing material. We may use your contact information to send newsletters from us and from our related companies.\n\nIn exceptional circumstances, we may be required to disclose information, such as when there are grounds to believe that the disclosure is necessary to prevent a threat to life or health, or for law enforcement purposes, or for the fulfillment of legal and regulatory requirements and requests.\n\nWe may share and permit the sharing of your data with third parties and our affiliates for any of the above-mentioned purposes, including but not limited to, facilitating your use of Mayura Services, completing a transaction with you, managing your account and our relationship with you, marketing and fulfilling any legal or regulatory requirements and requests as deemed necessary by us. In sharing your data with them, we endeavour to ensure that the third parties and our affiliates keep your data secure from unauthorised access, collection, use, disclosure, or similar risks and retain your data only for as long as they need your data to achieve the above mentioned purposes.",
          policy03:
              "You may communicate the withdrawal of your consent to the continued use or disclosure of your data for any of the purposes and in the manner as stated above at any time, or request the deletion of your data, by contacting our Data Protection Team.\n\nPlease note that if you communicate your withdrawal of your consent to our use or disclosure of your data for the purposes and in the manner as stated above, or request the deletion of your data, we may not be in a position to continue to provide our products or services to you or perform on any contract we have with you, and we will not be liable in the event that we do not continue to provide our products or services to, or perform our contract with you. Our legal rights and remedies are expressly reserved in such an event.",
          policy04:
              "It is important that the data you provide to us is accurate and up-to-date. You are responsible for informing us of changes to your data, or in the event you believe that the data we have about you is inaccurate, incomplete, misleading, or out-of-date. You can update your data anytime by accessing your account on Mayura. If you are unableto update your data through your account, you can do so by contacting our Data Protection Team.\n\nWe take steps to share the updates to your data with third parties and our affiliates with whom we have shared your data if your data is still necessary for the above-stated purposes.",
          policy05:
              "If you would like to request information about data which we have collected or inquire about the ways in which your data may have been used or disclosed by us within the past year, please contact our Data Protection Team. In order to facilitate processing of your request, it may be necessary for us to request further information relating to your request.\n\nWe reserve the right to charge a reasonable administrative fee for retrieving your data records. If so, we will inform you of the fee before processing your request.",
          policy06:
              "To safeguard your data from unauthorized access, collection, use, disclosure, copying, modification, disposal, or similar risks, we practice appropriate administrative, physical, and technical measures such as (a) restricting access to data to individuals who require access;(b) maintaining technology products to prevent unauthorized computer access; (c) deleting or anonymizing your data in compliance with the standards mandated by applicable law, when it is no longer needed for any legal or business purpose; and (d) using 128-bit SSL (secure sockets layer) encryption technology when processing your financial details.\n\nIf you believe that your privacy has been breached by Mayura, please contact our Data Protection Team.\n\nYou should be aware, however, that no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is completely secure. While security cannot be guaranteed, we strive to protect the security of your information and are constantly reviewing and enhancing our information security measures.\n\nYour password is the key to your account. Please use unique numbers, letters and special characters, and do not share your Mayura password with anyone. If you do share your password with others, you will be responsible for all actions taken in the name of your account and the consequences. If you lose control of your password, you may lose substantial control over your data submitted to Mayura. You could also be subject to legally binding actions taken on your behalf. Therefore, if your password has been compromised for any reason or if you have grounds to believe that your password has been compromised, you should immediately contact us and change your password. You are reminded to log out of your account and close the browser when you are finished with using a shared computer.",
          policy07:
              "We will only retain your data for as long as we are either required to by law or as is relevant for the purposes for which it was collected.\n\nWe will cease to retain your data, or remove the means by which the data can be associated with you, as soon as it is reasonable to assume that such retention no longer serves the purposes for which the data was collected, and is no longer necessary for any legal or business purpose.",
          policy08:
              "Mayura does not sell products for purchase by anyone under 18 years of age, nor does it intend to provide any of the Mayura Services to anyone under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect any data relating to anyone under 18 years of age.\n\nIf you are under 18 years old, you may use Mayura only with the consent and involvement of a parent or legal guardian.",
          policy09:
              "We or our authorised service providers may use cookies, web beacons, and other similar technologies for storing data to help provide you with a better, faster, safer, and more personalized experience when you use the Mayura Services.\n\nWhen you visit Mayura through your computer, mobile device, or any other device with internet connectivity, our company servers will automatically record data that your browser sends whenever you visit our website. This data may include: (a) your device\'s IP address;(b) browser type; (c) webpage you were visiting before you came to Mayura; (d) pages within Mayura which you visit; (e) time spent on those pages; (f) items and data searched for on Mayura; (g) access times and dates; and (h) other statistics.\n\nThis data is collected for analysis and evaluation in order to help us improve our website and the services and products we provide.\n\nCookies are small text files (typically made up of letters and numbers) placed in the memory of your browser or device when you visit a website or view a message. They allow us to recognize a particular device or browser and help us to personalize the content to match your preferred interests more quickly, and to make Mayura Services more convenient and useful for you. You are able to manage and delete cookies through your browser or device settings.\n\nWeb beacons are small graphic images that may be included on Mayura Services. They allow us to count users who have viewed these pages so that we can better understand your preference and interests.",
          policy10:
              "YOU ACKNOWLEDGE AND AGREE THAT MAYURA HAS THE RIGHT TO DISCLOSE YOUR DATA TO ANY LEGAL, REGULATORY, GOVERNMENTAL, TAX, LAW ENFORCEMENT OR OTHER AUTHORITIES OR THE RELEVANT RIGHT OWNERS, IF MAYURA HAS REASONABLE GROUNDS TO BELIEVE THAT DISCLOSURE OF YOUR DATA IS NECESSARY FOR THE PURPOSE OF MEETING ANY OBLIGATIONS,REQUIREMENTS, OR ARRANGEMENTS, WHETHER VOLUNTARY OR MANDATORY, AS A RESULT OF COOPERATING WITH AN ORDER, INVESTIGATION, AND/OR REQUEST OF ANY NATURE BY SUCH PARTIES. TO THE EXTENT PERMISSIBLE BY APPLICABLE LAW, YOU AGREE NOT TO TAKE ANY ACTION AND/OR WAIVE YOUR RIGHTS TO TAKE ANY ACTION AGAINST MAYURA FOR THE DISCLOSURE OF YOUR DATA IN THESE CIRCUMSTANCES.",
